      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">6.401</ph> Sealed bidding and competitive
proposals.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d400e13" class="- topic/p ">Sealed bidding and competitive proposals,
as described in <ph class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                     base="i1111055"
                     outputclass="fm:Parts"
                     class="- topic/xref ">parts  14</xref> 
               
            </ph>and <ph class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                     base="i1109360"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">15</xref>
            </ph>, are both acceptable
procedures for use under <ph class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1120051.dita#i1120051"
                     base="i1120051"
                     outputclass="fm:Subparts"
                     class="- topic/xref ">subparts  6.1</xref>
            </ph>, <ph class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1119917.dita#i1119917"
                     base="i1119917"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">6.2</xref>
            </ph>; and, when appropriate,
under <ph class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1119434.dita#i1119434"
                     base="i1119434"
                     outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                     class="- topic/xref ">subpart  6.3</xref>
            </ph>.</p>
         <ol id="d393e46" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d400e50" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Sealed
bids</i>. (See <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  14</xref> for
procedures.) Contracting officers shall solicit sealed bids if-</p>
               <ol id="d393e62" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e66" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Time
permits the solicitation, submission, and evaluation of sealed bids;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e75" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         The award
will be made on the basis of price and other price-related factors;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         It is not
necessary to conduct discussions with the responding offerors about
their bids; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e93" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         There is
a reasonable expectation of receiving more than one sealed bid.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d400e104" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   Competitive
proposals. (See <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref> for
procedures.)</p>
               <ol id="d393e113" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e117" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Contracting officers may request
competitive proposals if sealed bids are not appropriate <ph class="- topic/ph ">under paragraph (a) of this
section</ph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e129" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Because
of differences in areas such as law, regulations, and business practices,
it is generally necessary to conduct discussions with offerors relative
to proposed contracts to be made and performed outside the United
States and its outlying areas. Competitive proposals will therefore
be used for these contracts unless discussions are not required
and the use of sealed bids is otherwise appropriate.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
